byline.original: By STEPHEN CASTLE and ELLEN BARRY
byline.contributor: Stephen Castle reported from Brussels, and Ellen Barry from Kiev, Ukraine.

abstract: European Union officials are struggling to oppose sentencing of Yulia V Tymoshenko, Ukraine’s opposition leader, without driving Ukrainian Pres Viktor F Yanukovich closer to Moscow.
snippet: European Union officials are struggling to oppose the sentencing of Ukraine’s opposition leader without driving Ukraine’s president closer to Moscow.
lead_paragraph: European Union officials are struggling to oppose the sentencing of Ukraine’s opposition leader without driving Ukraine’s president closer to Moscow.

headline.main: Europe Cautiously Signals Its Displeasure Over a Prosecution in Ukraine

headline.seo: Europe Signals Its Ire at Ukraine’s President Yanukovich
